adjectives.description: sapless (comparative more sapless, superlative most sapless)

examples: Below, all their earthward-looking branches are sapless and shattered, splintered by the weight of many winters’ snows; above, they are still green and full of life, but their summits overtop all the deciduous trees around them, and in their companionship with heaven they are alone.

entries.meaning: (figuratively, of a person etc.) Lacking vivacity.
